<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="400" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,386,807]" pageId="8" pageNumber="400">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,386,411]" pageId="8" pageNumber="400">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Antenna slightly longer than head width; postpedicel mostly black; proximal portion of postpedicel reddish and about as long as distal portion (
<bibRefCitation author="d'Andretta" box="[675,870,422,447]" pageId="8" pageNumber="400" refString="d'Andretta, M. A. V. (1951) Contribuicao para o conhecimento da familia Mydaidae. Generos: Mydas F., 1794 e Messiasia, gen. n. (Diptera). Papeis avulsos de Zoologia, 10 (1), 1 - 76." type="journal article" year="1951">
d’Andretta 
<number box="[810,870,422,447]" pageId="8" pageNumber="400" value="1951.0">1951</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). Scutum velvety-black with four discrete white pruinose stripes. Male hind femur 
<number box="[539,574,458,483]" pageId="8" pageNumber="400" value="1.6">1.6</number>
times wider than hind tibia. 
<collectingCountry box="[898,954,458,483]" name="India" pageId="8" pageNumber="400">Hind</collectingCountry>
tibia with well-developed ventral keel and apical spur. 
<collectingCountry box="[287,343,494,519]" name="India" pageId="8" pageNumber="400">Hind</collectingCountry>
tarsomere 
<number box="[469,483,495,519]" pageId="8" pageNumber="400" value="1.0">1</number>
<number box="[491,526,494,519]" pageId="8" pageNumber="400" value="2.6">2.6</number>
times longer than wide, and 
<number box="[855,890,495,519]" pageId="8" pageNumber="400" value="1.7">1.7</number>
times longer than tarsomere 
<number box="[1220,1237,494,519]" pageId="8" pageNumber="400" value="5.0">5</number>
. Wing membrane opaque orange basally, yellow transparent apically; alula higher than wide. T 
<number box="[1011,1021,531,555]" pageId="8" pageNumber="400" value="1.0">1</number>
and T 
<number box="[1093,1107,531,555]" pageId="8" pageNumber="400" value="4.0">4</number>
black, remaining tergites and sternites with strong metallic blue. T 
<number box="[611,621,567,591]" pageId="8" pageNumber="400" value="1.0">1</number>
golden setulose, remaining with black setulae. Epandrial lamellae trapezoidal; external posterior extremity acute, but not prolonged as a spine (
<bibRefCitation author="d'Andretta" box="[1035,1225,602,627]" pageId="8" pageNumber="400" refString="d'Andretta, M. A. V. (1951) Contribuicao para o conhecimento da familia Mydaidae. Generos: Mydas F., 1794 e Messiasia, gen. n. (Diptera). Papeis avulsos de Zoologia, 10 (1), 1 - 76." type="journal article" year="1951">
d’Andretta 
<number box="[1167,1225,602,627]" pageId="8" pageNumber="400" value="1951.0">1951</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 
<number box="[1287,1333,603,627]" pageId="8" pageNumber="400" value="103.0">103</number>
); phallus with distinct dorsal crest but with inconspicuous lateral projections (
<bibRefCitation author="d'Andretta" box="[914,1101,638,663]" pageId="8" pageNumber="400" refString="d'Andretta, M. A. V. (1951) Contribuicao para o conhecimento da familia Mydaidae. Generos: Mydas F., 1794 e Messiasia, gen. n. (Diptera). Papeis avulsos de Zoologia, 10 (1), 1 - 76." type="journal article" year="1951">
d’Andretta 
<number box="[1043,1101,638,663]" pageId="8" pageNumber="400" value="1951.0">1951</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 
<number box="[1158,1204,638,663]" pageId="8" pageNumber="400" value="152.0">152</number>
). Female S 
<number box="[1328,1357,639,663]" pageId="8" pageNumber="400" value="10.0">10</number>
poorly sclerotized medially; sclerite at base of spermathecal ducts narrower than cerci (
<figureCitation box="[1048,1115,674,699]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="14.[151,249,1861,1883]" captionTargetBox="[151,1432,303,1830]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[151,1436,303,1839]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 4. Male terminalia of Gauromydas. A – C: Gauromydas mateus sp. nov. (holotype, MNHN). D – F: Gauromydas mystaceus (MPEG). G – I: Gauromydas papaveroi sp nov. (holotype, MZUSP). A, D, G: epandrium and proctiger, dorsal view; B, E, H: gonocoxite-hypandrial complex and associate structures, dorsal view; C, F, I: gonocoxite-hypandrial complex and associate structures, lateral view; J, Gauromydas heros, phallus and associate structures, lateral view. Abbreviations: lph: phallic lateral projection; ph: phallus; phc: phallic crest; gxd: dorsal prolongation of the gonocoxite-hypandrial complex (Calhau et al. 2014). Scale bars: 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/245787/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="400">
Fig. 
<number box="[1100,1115,675,699]" pageId="8" pageNumber="400" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
H). Length: 
<quantity box="[1252,1376,674,699]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.4" metricValueMax="2.5" metricValueMin="2.3" pageId="8" pageNumber="400" unit="mm" value="24.0" valueMax="25.0" valueMin="23.0">23–25 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
